# Transactions in Record Request Event Hooks #3146 - GitHub
created: 2023-08-16, last updated: 2025-05-23, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/3146)

*Just in case someone stumble here - option to wrap the request hooks chain in a transaction was added in PocketBase v0.23+.
For example:*
- Go:
```
app.OnRecordCreateRequest("users").BindFunc(func(e *core.RecordRequestEvent) error {
originalApp := e.App
txErr := e.App.RunInTransaction(func(txApp core.App) error {
e.App = txApp
// do something before the create...
// execute the create
err := e.Next()
if err != nil {
return err
}
// do something after the create...
return nil
})
e.App = originalApp
return txErr
})
```
- JS:
```
onRecordCreateRequest((e) => {
let originalApp = e.app
try {
e.app.runInTransaction((txApp) => {
e.app = txApp
// do something before the create...
// execute the create
e.next()
// do something after the create...
})
} finally {
e.app = originalApp
}
}, "users")
```

